model.description: Paul Gauguin Cruises has deep roots in the islands. Pacific Beachcomber owns the cruise line and also operates the four InterContinental properties in the region; Maitai resorts on Bora Bora, Rangiroa, and Huahine; and The Brando on Tetiaroa. The PG’s officers and crew have vast expertise when it comes to the history, culture, and ecosystems of these islands. Every voyage has a lineup of onboard lecturers—such as anthropologist and archaeologist Mark Eddowes (who also leads Trails of the Ancients Trek, one of the most popular excursions on Moorea) and Dr. Michael Poole, a marine biologist who takes guests out on the water to encounter sea life.
